The 1983 Set of the Anglican Grammar School, Iju/Itaogbolu, Akure North, Ondo State has completed the renovation of science laboratories for the school, as their first Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) project to mark their second reunion. President of the 1983 Set, Prof Christopher Rotimi Falegan, said the laboratory was picked as the first project because the building was in a dilapidated condition. Falegan, who was re-elected at the reunion party, said: “The project was done due to the immediate need of the school when the principal was contacted. The project cost N1.3 million.”   Tackle insecurity with technology, says ANCOPSS     Council fetes 200 widows, aged     ‘Two million Nigerians get N10b monthly stipends’   The school principal, Mrs Modupe Dolapo Omotoba thanked the alumni . The Chairman of the Project Committee, Mr Dickson Sunday Abiodun, said “we feel grateful to the Lord for given us the grace to come in where it is necessary for the school and the pupils of our alma mater,” he said. - Advertisement - Mr Olaniyi Apata who joined online from London and Mrs Funmi Fadiya from Canada also congratulated the executive and the project committee for job well done. Rev. Canon Yemi Akinyemi hailed the alumni for managing the association despite all odds.